abstract: >-
  BenGER is a benchmark for German legal reasoning, comprising three thematic
  subsets — Benchathon (collaboratively graded long-form legal analyses across
  civil, public, and criminal law), ZJS (published exam-style cases from the
  Zeitschrift für das Juristische Studium), and Grundprinzipien (foundational
  legal-principle multiple-choice items). Twelve LLM systems were evaluated
  with both automatic metrics and rubric-aligned LLM-as-a-Judge scoring;
  Benchathon further includes a seven-reviewer human grading layer used to
  validate the judge. The dataset is released as a single Hugging Face
  dataset (`SebastianNagl/benger`) with three configurations.
